WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:06.000
Hey, good morning, family. Thank you for joining us again today. We're going to pray over your needs

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.920
today. There are many of you, like this family right here, who are believing for so

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:18.960
much. We received that in the mail today, and I'm just like, 'Wow.'There are so many of you

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:24.960
believing for a breakthrough for your loved ones. I mean, I have other

00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:30.400
photos right here. There are so many families. Like I said, we have

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:36.160
photos now all over our car. We drive around and look like we have photos everywhere

00:00:36.160 --> 00:00:40.240
that we pray over when we're driving around. People send them to us, and

00:00:40.240 --> 00:00:47.280
they need a breakthrough. These people are desperate; they need a touch from the Father.

00:00:47.280 --> 00:00:53.280
They don't need a stale word from a pastor where you go on a Wednesday night or a Sunday and you

00:00:53.280 --> 00:01:00.960
walk away thinking, 'What was that? Why did I waste my thirty minutes? Why did I waste

00:01:00.960 --> 00:01:06.560
an hour? I could have gotten more watching a YouTube video than I got from that.'I don't want to waste

00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:13.840
people's time. I say, 'God, we need a fresh river. We need fresh glory.'We

00:01:13.840 --> 00:01:19.040
need to get this old vinegar out of these old wineskins and put the anointing of the Holy

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:26.560
Ghost on us. Rub that oil down into that pouch of who we are, that vessel,

00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:33.040
making it pliable again. Because when you put that anointing oil on that vessel and rub it in, making that

00:01:33.040 --> 00:01:39.760
leather pouch pliable again, it makes it so

00:01:39.760 --> 00:01:47.600
if you put the new wine in it, it won't crack and bust. The oil and the anointing of the Holy Ghost

00:01:47.600 --> 00:01:55.360
is what makes us brand new every single day. You have to have that glory—the outward honey glow.

00:01:55.360 --> 00:02:01.280
That's why I told Diana—we talk about it all the time—I want it so much that it never turns

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:06.560
off, that they have to put a drape around my head because people ask, 'What is going on with that

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:14.080
dude's face? He's glowing with the glory.'I tell my children, 'We represent the Father.'So,

00:02:14.080 --> 00:02:20.080
we act like the Father; we demonstrate ourselves as the Father would. I know we're all a work

00:02:20.080 --> 00:02:26.880
in progress, but I'm just desperate for Him. I'm desperate for Him. And I know what's coming.

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:32.800
I know a great shaking is coming to awaken you. And I will sound the alarm, just like Jeremiah, to tell

00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:38.800
you all that God is coming. And you have to get your house in order because we're running out

00:02:38.800 --> 00:02:45.520
of time. Thank God we're not like we were back then; we're under more grace. I get it, but

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:52.720
I'm telling you all, a great shaking is coming. What's coming is not God's judgment. Ladies and gentlemen, what's

00:02:52.720 --> 00:02:59.280
coming is not judgment; it's a Father correcting a child who is spoiled. It's the Father who is

00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:05.840
correcting a child who has gone wayward, saying, 'You've gone off the road, buddy, and

00:03:05.840 --> 00:03:11.840
I want you to come back over here in the fold.'The ninety-nine sheep are over here, and you're the one,

00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:18.000
and I'm trying to snatch that one. There are a lot of ones, but He's trying to grab a hold of those ones.

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:23.120
And He's like, 'You got way off track, and you're fifty miles away from where you're

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:31.760
supposed to be. But I have more mercy and more love to let you have an extended time to bring them in.'Your

00:03:31.760 --> 00:03:36.960
unsaved loved ones—the people who are so wayward that you think, 'Man, they're never

00:03:36.960 --> 00:03:43.680
coming in.'No, all things are possible to him who believes. Ladies and gentlemen, glory to God!

00:03:43.680 --> 00:03:48.880
All things are possible to him who believes. You've just got to believe it. You've got to put your faith

00:03:48.880 --> 00:03:53.040
into motion. What are you believing for today? You say, 'Well, I'm believing for finances.'Then sow

00:03:53.040 --> 00:03:59.760
a seed. Every seed produces after its own kind. What are you believing God for today?

00:03:59.760 --> 00:04:06.320
David said, 'I give nothing that doesn't cost me something. If it doesn't cost you something, then it isn't

00:04:06.320 --> 00:04:11.600
precious to you.'And David gave when it hurt, and the Bible says that. And that's where

00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:17.120
I've tried to say, 'What's my chokehold? Where am I at with the Lord concerning this?'People say,

00:04:17.120 --> 00:04:22.880
'I don't believe in tithing because it's under the Old Covenant.'I believe in giving

00:04:22.880 --> 00:04:32.480
God something to work with. I believe in giving God—if the farmer sows a seed to reap a harvest,

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:38.960
then I'm going to sow a seed to reap a harvest. If I have a need, I sow a seed. That's what we always

00:04:38.960 --> 00:04:45.920
do in this household. Where do you give? You give to your local church. You give to where you're

00:04:45.920 --> 00:04:51.920
being fed spiritually. You give to the people who are pouring into you spiritually; that's where you

00:04:51.920 --> 00:04:57.840
give. So, where your pastor is and where the people are who are ministering to you on

00:04:57.840 --> 00:05:03.520
a day-to-day basis—those are the people you give to. Why? Because that's what keeps the local church

00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:09.600
going. If you don't have a local church in your area, you have to have a prayer covering.

00:05:09.600 --> 00:05:16.160
That's what changes things. When that body comes together, you come as an army in that

00:05:16.160 --> 00:05:21.520
community. So, you keep that local church going. You keep the people who are feeding you going

00:05:21.520 --> 00:05:28.720
so that they keep feeding you, so they are able to distribute out and help others. It's

00:05:28.720 --> 00:05:34.400
like a storehouse. You bring your tithe to the storehouse. You bring that to the storehouse.

00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:38.480
Where the storehouse is, is where you're getting fed. That's where the grain is, and all the things

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:42.480
you put in the storehouse. You bring the tithe to the storehouse.

00:05:42.480 --> 00:05:48.720
Your local church is your storehouse where you're getting fed. You take care of that pastor; you take

00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:52.720
care of them, and then you make sure they're able to have community outreach or whatever

00:05:52.720 --> 00:05:58.160
they're doing. I just believe that that's what we do in these last days to help the

00:05:58.160 --> 00:06:02.320
local church out. We help it. You say, 'Well, we don't have to tithe.'No, but you still

00:06:02.320 --> 00:06:08.880
give. I don't believe there's a curse on people if you don't tithe, okay, but I believe

00:06:08.880 --> 00:06:17.120
that God said He rebukes the devourer for our sake. And if He did it back then, He'll do it again.

00:06:17.120 --> 00:06:24.000
And I want a blessing on my money. I want prosperity and His blessing on it—my heart hearing Him say,

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:31.600
'Brandon, well done, thou good and faithful servant. You did everything you could;

00:06:31.600 --> 00:06:36.720
you helped stretch the Kingdom of God throughout the whole world.'Most

00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:41.280
people don't want to give. Most people are stingy with it, and they say, 'Well, when I get more money,

00:06:41.280 --> 00:06:46.240
I'll give and do this and that.'No, we started

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:51.200
tithing because we had to. I don't know why I got off on this; I guess it's because Braden told me

00:06:51.200 --> 00:06:55.920
something. We get some emails where people say, 'We don't believe in tithing. What do you believe about it?'Well,

00:06:55.920 --> 00:07:01.840
this is my opinion: I believe in tithing. I believe in giving my ten percent. I believe in giving

00:07:01.840 --> 00:07:08.240
over the ten percent as much as I can because I know what it takes to get the gospel out. It seems like

00:07:08.240 --> 00:07:13.280
I've worked for churches my whole life. We knew what it took to get the

00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:18.560
bills paid at the church; we knew what it took to get the flyers out and all the staff

00:07:18.560 --> 00:07:25.120
paid. It takes millions of dollars. Most people say, 'Well, I gave my ten bucks.'Well,

00:07:25.120 --> 00:07:30.960
the church was thankful for the ten dollars, but there were a lot of tippers. You're believing

00:07:30.960 --> 00:07:37.840
that you can step into the overflow, for God to speak to you about abundant things, but that

00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:44.640
comes out of whether He can trust you with it. If God can't trust you with the ten percent that you have

00:07:44.640 --> 00:07:48.960
to tithe to Him, He's not going to show you the greater works. I'm telling you, I'm just

00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:54.000
being real with you all. I'm just telling you all the facts, and most people don't want to hear it. You say,

00:07:54.000 --> 00:08:00.400
'Well, I'm qualified because I gave my five bucks to the Lord today.'You tipped God.

00:08:00.400 --> 00:08:05.840
You made a quarter of a million dollars last year, and you gave ten dollars. Whoop-de-do! I mean, I'm

00:08:05.840 --> 00:08:10.880
just saying. You think that you're qualified for God to tell you the secret

00:08:10.880 --> 00:08:18.720
things because you gave your hundred bucks and you made $250,000 last year? Seriously, it

00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:26.160
comes out of sacrifice. David said, 'I didn't give God anything that didn't cost me something.'So

00:08:26.160 --> 00:08:34.080
you are expecting God to pour out his blessing on you in a dump truck load, but you gave in a

00:08:34.080 --> 00:08:41.520
thimble load. And you're asking God to do something mightily in your finances whenever

00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:48.560
it's so backwards is what I'm trying to tell y'all. Seek ye first the kingdom and

00:08:48.560 --> 00:08:53.280
his righteousness, and all these things will be added unto you. Give, and it shall be given

00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:58.000
unto you: good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will men give into your bosom.

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:02.880
And so that's just what Diana and I believe. You ask us or tell you, I don't

00:09:02.880 --> 00:09:07.680
like talking about money stuff because you're like, 'Well, you know you're after money.'No, I don't care; I

00:09:07.680 --> 00:09:12.560
honest to goodness don't care. This is because people ask me, 'What do you believe about this, Brandon?'And

00:09:12.560 --> 00:09:19.120
this is what Diana and I believe. We believe in the power of the seed. We believe

00:09:19.120 --> 00:09:24.400
in the power that you give and it shall be given unto you: good measure, pressed down, shaken together,

00:09:24.400 --> 00:09:29.120
and running over will men give into your bosom. That's what Diana and I believe. We believe that

00:09:29.120 --> 00:09:34.960
God is a rewarder of those that diligently seek Him. Not just with my time and prayer,

00:09:34.960 --> 00:09:42.480
but seeking Him with my finances. God, if I give, you said that you give me 30, 60, 100-fold. That's

00:09:42.480 --> 00:09:47.680
what you said in your word. You said in Malachi—I'm not putting myself underneath

00:09:47.680 --> 00:09:53.040
the old covenant, Lord—but you said back then that you rebuke the devourer for my sake. So Father, how

00:09:53.040 --> 00:09:58.880
much more will you rebuke the devourer for my sake now? I'm not underneath the old covenant, but I'm

00:09:58.880 --> 00:10:04.160
underneath the new, but I still want to believe in the blessing. I still want to believe in helping

00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:10.640
the church out. And it's a heart thing. It's a heart thing. And I say, 'God, my heart is for you. My heart

00:10:10.640 --> 00:10:16.480
is for the gospel. I want to help Billy Burke out. I want to help missionaries out. I want to help them.'If

00:10:16.480 --> 00:10:21.680
you're going out and praying for the sick and seeing people recover, I would like to help you.

00:10:21.680 --> 00:10:27.520
If I see that you're doing something major for God, I want to help you. I see the cause, I see

00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:32.480
the anointing, and you sow into the anointing. Do you give all at one place? No, I split

00:10:32.480 --> 00:10:39.680
my seed a lot of times and I help each ministry out. I help pastors, prophets, teachers,

00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:43.920
evangelists, and all this. And I try, even if it's just five bucks whatever, until you grow. You say,

00:10:43.920 --> 00:10:48.560
'Here, here, here.'But I try to sow the big one. And then the one that feeds me

00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:55.200
the most I give them the most, right, because I'm getting impartation from it. Above tithe I try to

00:10:55.200 --> 00:11:00.240
help out. So that's what I'm trying to say. And maybe that'll make sense for some of

00:11:00.240 --> 00:11:05.040
y'all, but you ask me my opinion, what Diana and I do. And that's exactly what we've done.

00:11:05.040 --> 00:11:10.560
And we've done it for a while now saying, 'God help me because I'm not going to be manipulated.''Well,

00:11:10.560 --> 00:11:15.600
all your tithe should come to my church because you're a part of my flock and you need

00:11:15.600 --> 00:11:20.320
to give all your money here.'Whatever I'm going to do, I'm going to do what the Holy Spirit tells

00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:25.040
me to do. And people get ticked off about that, but whatever. I just follow the voice of

00:11:25.040 --> 00:11:30.400
the Lord for our life. And what he tells me to do is I give it. If you're not underneath the curse of

00:11:30.400 --> 00:11:35.920
the old covenant and it's not there, then I'm not going to be manipulated about my tithe

00:11:35.920 --> 00:11:40.320
either. I will not sit there and have you tell me all

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:46.080
this stuff where I should be giving my money. I will follow the Holy Spirit and he will show me

00:11:46.080 --> 00:11:51.040
that which is to come. And when you do that and you're led by the Holy Spirit

00:11:51.040 --> 00:11:57.680
you'll always be blessed. Follow the Holy Spirit in what the word tells you to do. Give to

00:11:57.680 --> 00:12:04.080
where you're being fed. Give to the ministries that are feeding you. And I'm telling you, God

00:12:04.080 --> 00:12:10.320
will anoint you. Be led by the spirit of God when it comes to your giving. There's a lot of different

00:12:10.320 --> 00:12:14.080
theories; there's a lot of different theologies when it comes to this. And everybody's about it

00:12:14.080 --> 00:12:17.920
because everybody wants the money. And I'll be real with you, that's what I've seen a lot in the body

00:12:17.920 --> 00:12:26.640
of Christ. A lot of people want the money and they go, 'I feel that if you give this $58 seed and

00:12:26.640 --> 00:12:32.160
this $58 blessing you're going to get a miracle.'I don't get into all that stuff. I just give where

00:12:32.160 --> 00:12:38.160
I'm led to give to help when God tells me to give. And that's exactly what Diana and I do. And

00:12:38.160 --> 00:12:46.800
I am not manipulated by emotion. Never give out of emotion.

00:12:47.360 --> 00:12:54.160
Give by the spirit of the Lord leading you. Does that make sense? If you're led by your emotions,

00:12:54.160 --> 00:12:58.800
your emotions change all the time. You can give a seed and you'll be like, 'Why in the world did

00:12:58.800 --> 00:13:04.320
I just give that?'five minutes later. Sometimes it's the devil trying to torment you, but sometimes it is

00:13:04.320 --> 00:13:11.120
because you acted out in flesh. And I'm not going to be, 'Well, you know, I heard the sob story

00:13:11.120 --> 00:13:17.600
about that and it was really sad at church and I gave it.'I'm not going to give out of emotion.

00:13:17.600 --> 00:13:24.000
I'm giving by the spirit of God leading me. Does that make sense? When you're led by the spirit of

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:31.680
the Lord there is a blessing behind it. But there truly is a 30, 60, and 100-fold. And you

00:13:31.680 --> 00:13:37.920
find the 100-fold grounds, you found a nugget. If you find the 60-fold, you still found a really good one. Thirty

00:13:37.920 --> 00:13:44.160
is okay; it's a return. But I'm serious, I told the Lord, I said, 'Where is the 100-fold

00:13:44.160 --> 00:13:50.160
ground? Show me how to sow into that because I want to be the farmer that sows into the manure

00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:58.880
that gets back the big harvest. I sow to reap, I sow.'They said, 'Well, do you give to get?'Well,

00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:06.400
yeah, basically, but I'm not giving it out of that attitude. I'm giving to sow because God says he

00:14:06.400 --> 00:14:13.360
loves a cheerful giver, but he gives back 30, 60. It's his system. So I'm sowing into it saying,

00:14:13.360 --> 00:14:22.640
'God, show me how to reap the maximum reward.'And if this

00:14:22.640 --> 00:14:29.840
is stony ground, run. 'Well, their ministry died.'Well, it wasn't me, it's stony ground. It doesn't need

00:14:29.840 --> 00:14:35.600
to be there anyway. I mean, I'm just being real. Let them move on and do something else. Sell on

00:14:35.600 --> 00:14:41.280
eBay; it's a good living. If their

00:14:41.280 --> 00:14:46.800
ground is stony they shouldn't be in ministry anyway. If it's sandy soil and

00:14:46.800 --> 00:14:53.840
it's bad soil, why are they preaching then? Close the doors down and go on. We

00:14:53.840 --> 00:14:58.400
need people that are filled with and controlled by the Holy Ghost in these last days. We don't need to be

00:14:58.400 --> 00:15:03.280
wasting people's time just doing it because it's all that I've ever known how to do. Do something

00:15:03.280 --> 00:15:11.200
else. Be a door greeter at Walmart. I mean, I don't mean to be rude but that's just real. Don't waste

00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:17.200
my time. And that's why I don't want to waste your time.

00:15:17.200 --> 00:15:23.440
We're just real. I've seen it all. I've been around some big ministers,

00:15:23.440 --> 00:15:28.640
some of the big guys. And you look at them and you go, 'What's real and what's not? Is

00:15:28.640 --> 00:15:34.640
there an anointing here or not?'I want you all to be successful. I want you to go

00:15:34.640 --> 00:15:40.240
from glory to glory and not keep going around the mountain expecting different results every single

00:15:40.240 --> 00:15:45.360
time. For 40 years they wandered in the wilderness. For 40 years they wandered and they never said,

00:15:45.360 --> 00:15:51.520
'Why am I still going through what we're going through?''Moses, why are we still walking around this mountain?'And

00:15:51.520 --> 00:15:55.600
you go through another year and he's like, 'Well, the whole generation has to die because

00:15:55.600 --> 00:16:01.360
of unbelief and we're going to raise up the Joshuas and the Calebs to go and take the land because we

00:16:01.360 --> 00:16:06.720
really aren't the size of grasshoppers to these giants.'We're going to go and take the land. Who

00:16:06.720 --> 00:16:13.120
wants to be a land grabber? Us! I don't want to live in the valley of the shadow of death

00:16:13.120 --> 00:16:19.760
anymore. I want to live on the high peaks with Jesus Christ in these last days. I want

00:16:19.760 --> 00:16:27.840
to know how to go from glory to glory to glory. I'm so tired. You

00:16:27.840 --> 00:16:33.680
listen to all these sermons and you hear them and you know, is this really working? I

00:16:33.680 --> 00:16:38.800
want to see it. I want to see fruit. When your mom and dad and great-grandparents,

00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:43.600
and they all live from paycheck to paycheck and you give because

00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:47.760
they can preach the money out of your wallet and they get you all excited about it, and you walk

00:16:47.760 --> 00:16:55.600
away and you're still broke. You're still broke and it's frustrating and you go and you listen

00:16:55.600 --> 00:17:00.000
to it and you hear the prosperity gospel and you hear all this stuff. And God is a God that

00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:05.440
is abundantly rewarding those that diligently seek him. And he wants you to have 30, 60, and 100-fold, but

00:17:05.440 --> 00:17:13.120
you're giving it into bad ground. And you walk away going, 'What gives, Lord? How come you haven't met

00:17:13.120 --> 00:17:19.600
my stuff?'Because we're still looking for the mailbox mentality. We're looking for, "Well, God,

00:17:19.600 --> 00:17:25.440
where's my angel with the bag of money in his hand?"like that preacher talked about. I'm

00:17:25.440 --> 00:17:29.600
telling you that I've heard of miracles happening, and God does that, ladies and gentlemen. And God

00:17:29.600 --> 00:17:36.960
will do that; it's an exception, not the rule. He will anoint your hands to prosper. He

00:17:36.960 --> 00:17:43.680
will abundantly bless your hands to do something. Put your boat into motion. God isn't looking for

00:17:43.680 --> 00:17:50.560
the talents; you could either bury the talents, or you can make the talents work for you by

00:17:50.560 --> 00:17:58.000
doing something with your hands, asking Him for a creative idea to get wealth. "God, show me how to

00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:03.760
get this."I was the guy, I'm telling you, for a long time. As a janitor sitting back there, I was going,

00:18:03.760 --> 00:18:11.040
"Lord, Lord, teach me how some sister will walk up and give me $100 today because we're desperate for it."And

00:18:11.040 --> 00:18:15.600
that's a miracle for someone to hear it on their heart to give you

00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:22.720
some money, but God wants to make you a fisherman to go out and get it

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:28.800
yourself. Teach me how to do it. And that's whenever the Lord told me, "Brennan, I'll teach you

00:18:28.800 --> 00:18:35.040
how to flip cars. Go out and buy this car that's broken over here, and pay your dad or

00:18:35.040 --> 00:18:40.240
whoever to put that timing belt on that car and fix it, and you can make it."I'm

00:18:40.240 --> 00:18:46.560
telling you, listen, I bought a car for, I think it was like 500 bucks—you weren't even born yet—and

00:18:46.560 --> 00:18:51.680
the Lord said, "Buy that car; it just needs a new timing belt on it and

00:18:51.680 --> 00:18:57.760
it's going to run."I bought it for 500 bucks and I sold it for $3,000. But at that

00:18:57.760 --> 00:19:02.080
time, that $500 seed for that car that needed a new timing belt—Of course, there was nothing

00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:08.080
else wrong with this car, and this was a long time ago—that $3,000 was a lot of money to us. So

00:19:08.080 --> 00:19:14.080
He said, "A man with a white shirt... after you fix this car, a man with a white shirt..."I prayed in the

00:19:14.080 --> 00:19:18.800
spirit. The Lord said, "A man with a white shirt is going to knock on your door tomorrow, and he's

00:19:18.800 --> 00:19:24.080
going to buy the car because the for-sale sign was on it."This Hispanic man walked up;

00:19:24.080 --> 00:19:29.360
he had a white shirt on just like the Lord said, and he said, "I've come to buy the car. I have cash."He

00:19:29.360 --> 00:19:38.720
